    <id>https://github.com/andrii-kryvoviaz/slink/releases/tag/v1.4.5</id>
    <title>New release for Slink: v1.4.5</title>
    <updated>2025-01-05T11:56:26-05:00</updated>
    <author>
      <name>andrii-kryvoviaz/slink</name>
    </author>
    <content>&lt;p&gt;This patch reverts back to the root user by default but keeps the possibility to alter this behavior manually. See related issue #38.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The decision was made because I donâ€™t want to overcomplicate the deployment for new users, so non-root user becomes a &lt;a href="https://docs.slinkapp.io/reference/04-non-root-container-user/"&gt;feature&lt;/a&gt; rather than the default behavior.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Here is an example of a Docker Compose configuration for running as a non-root user:
&lt;code&gt;yaml
services:
  slink:
    user: slink
    # Your other configurations&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;[!NOTE]
By running as a non-root user, you will need to resolve permission issues for mounted volumes manually, as nothing can be done at the container level.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Full Changelog&lt;/strong&gt;: https://github.com/andrii-kryvoviaz/slink/compare/v1.4.4...v1.4.5&lt;/p&gt;</content>
    <link href="https://github.com/andrii-kryvoviaz/slink/releases/tag/v1.4.5" rel="alternate"/>
  </entry>
